The paper focuses on the collection and analysis of social media data, specifically Facebook data, which falls under the category of social media and computational social science (cs.SI, cs.SOC). The paper also discusses issues related to data privacy and security, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of surveys and the comparison of survey data with social media data, which could fall under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
